Durable Objects guarantee single-threaded access — no race conditions. They're ideal for: rate limiters, collaborative editing, game state, distributed locks, and WebSocket coordination. Each object can hold a WebSocket connection for real-time use cases.

React Native's StyleSheet looks like CSS but has critical differences. Web CSS intuitions often lead to bugs.

**Difference 1 — No cascading, no inheritance:**
```tsx
// WEB: child inherits font from parent
<div style={{ fontFamily: 'Inter', color: 'blue' }}>
  <span>I'm blue Inter</span>  {/* Inherits both */}
</div>

// REACT NATIVE: No inheritance except Text inside Text
<View style={{ fontFamily: 'Inter' }}>
  <Text>I'm NOT Inter</Text>  {/* Does not inherit */}
</View>

// Fix: Style each Text individually or use a custom Text component
const BaseText = ({ style, ...props }: TextProps) => (
  <Text style={[{ fontFamily: 'Inter', color: '#111' }, style]} {...props} />
);
```

**Difference 2 — Flexbox defaults are different:**
```tsx
// WEB default: flexDirection: 'row'
// RN default: flexDirection: 'column'

// WEB: width/height in various units (%, vw, rem)
// RN: only unitless numbers (density-independent pixels) or '%'
<View style={{ width: 100, height: '50%' }} />  // 100dp, 50% of parent
// <View style={{ width: '10rem' }} />  // ERROR: not supported
```

**Difference 3 — No shorthand properties:**
```tsx
// WEB: margin: '10px 20px'
// RN: Must use individual properties
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    // margin: '10 20',  // ERROR
    marginVertical: 10,
    marginHorizontal: 20,
    // Or:
    marginTop: 10,
    marginBottom: 10,
    marginLeft: 20,
    marginRight: 20,
  },
});
```

**Difference 4 — Shadow syntax differs per platform:**
```tsx
const shadow = Platform.select({
  ios: {
    shadowColor: '#000',
    shadowOffset: { width: 0, height: 2 },
    shadowOpacity: 0.1,
    shadowRadius: 4,
  },
  android: {
    elevation: 4,  // Android uses elevation, not shadow properties
  },
});
```

**Difference 5 — No z-index stacking context like CSS:**
In RN, `zIndex` only works between siblings. There's no stacking context hierarchy. Later siblings render on top of earlier siblings by default.

Vercel Edge Middleware intercepts requests before they reach your application. Use it for bot detection, redirects, and request modification.

```typescript
// middleware.ts
import { NextRequest, NextResponse, userAgent } from 'next/server';

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico).*)'],
};

// Known bot patterns
const BOT_PATTERNS = [
  /bot/i, /crawler/i, /spider/i, /scraper/i,
  /facebookexternalhit/i, /Twitterbot/i, /LinkedInBot/i,
  /Slackbot/i, /Discordbot/i,
];

export function middleware(req: NextRequest) {
  const ua = userAgent(req);
  const isBot = ua.isBot || BOT_PATTERNS.some(p => p.test(ua.ua || ''));

  // Serve pre-rendered pages to bots for SEO
  if (isBot && req.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/app/')) {
    // Redirect bots to a pre-rendered version
    const url = req.nextUrl.clone();
    url.pathname = `/bot${url.pathname}`;
    return NextResponse.rewrite(url);
  }

  // Block suspicious requests
  const ip = req.headers.get('x-forwarded-for')?.split(',')[0] || req.ip;
  const suspiciousHeaders = !req.headers.get('accept-language');

  if (suspiciousHeaders && !isBot) {
    // Log suspicious request
    console.log(`Suspicious request from ${ip}: ${req.nextUrl.pathname}`);
  }

  // Device-based routing
  if (ua.device.type === 'mobile' && req.nextUrl.pathname === '/') {
    const url = req.nextUrl.clone();
    url.pathname = '/mobile';
    return NextResponse.rewrite(url);
  }

  // Add security headers
  const response = NextResponse.next();
  response.headers.set('X-Content-Type-Options', 'nosniff');
  response.headers.set('X-Frame-Options', 'DENY');
  response.headers.set('Referrer-Policy', 'strict-origin-when-cross-origin');

  return response;
}
```

Middleware runs at the edge (CDN locations) before your serverless functions or static files. Keep middleware lightweight — it has a 1MB code size limit on Vercel and should complete in <50ms. Use `NextResponse.rewrite` to change routing without changing the user-visible URL.

